Do you know what is PET SCAN.

A Pet Scan shows how the brain and its tissues are working. Other imaging tests, such as magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) and computed tomography (CT) scans only reveal the structure of the brain. It uses a radioactive substance called a tracer to look for disease or injury in the brain.

You know what the best part of the gym and medical world is? The acceptance. It's an odd thing to think about, but it's really why a lot of us keep coming back! I know I've experienced it, intact I even experienced it today in both worlds. Today I walked into my final 3 weeks of placement before exams, which is in a small hospital in the emergency department that I'd been to before for 8 weeks. I walked in, and within a second I got one of the docs saying "aye he's back", to which I replied "I liked it too much, couldn't keep me away". Everyone still remembered me, everyone knew my name and greeted me like an old friend. There was no competition or anything, this was purely a team environment and we all gelled well. Post that I went to the gym, on arrival I got greeted with "you go go to Oxford now do ya mate" (I collect uni jumper and alas wear them to the gym #sendmeyourunijumper). Then on entering the gym, I got greeted by name by at least 5 other people there, by name, asking about my day. This sense of belonging is amazing! I've never had it prior to the gym outside of my family. I can tell you it's one of the best feelings ever.
